{{primary sources|date=February 2018}}
'''Henry E. Allison''' is an eminent scholar of [[Immanuel Kant]].<ref>[[Brian Leiter]], [http://leiterreports.typepad.com/blog/2016/02/best-anglophone-and-german-kant-scholars-since-1945.html Best Anglophone and German Kant scholars since 1945? (February 18, 2016)]</ref> He is Emeritus Professor of the [[University of California, San Diego]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://philosophy.ucsd.edu/people/faculty.html|title=UC San Diego Philosophy Faculty|website=philosophy.ucsd.edu|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref> and [[Boston University]].<ref name="bu.edu">{{cite web|url=http://www.bu.edu/philo/profiles/henry-allison/|title=Henry Allison »  Philosophy  - Blog Archive  - Boston University|website=www.bu.edu|accessdate=3 February 2018}}</ref> His interests are [[Immanuel Kant]], [[Baruch Spinoza]], [[German idealism]], [[18th-century philosophy|18th]] and [[19th-century philosophy|19th century philosophy]].<ref name="bu.edu"/>

