{{Sangam literature}}
'''Ponmudiyār''' ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: பொன்முடியார்) was a poetess of the [[Sangam period]], to whom 4 verses of the Sangam literature have been attributed, including verse 14 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="Vedanayagam_Urai">{{cite book | last = Vedanayagam | first = Rama | author-link = | title = திருவள்ளுவ மாலை மூலமும் எளிய உரை விளக்கமும் [Tiruvalluva Maalai: Moolamum Eliya Urai Vilakkamum] | publisher = Manimekalai Prasuram | series = | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 2017 | location = Chennai | pages = 26–27 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Biography== Ponmudiyar lived during the time of the [[Chera dynasty|Chera]] king Thagadur Erindha Peruncheral Irumporai.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = அகநானூறு, புறநானூறு [Agananuru, Purananuru] | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 3 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 413 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> She was the well-wisher of the [[Athiyaman|Athiyaman king]] Nedumananji, who is known for giving an eternal [[gooseberry]] fruit to [[Avvaiyar I]], and has written in praise of him.<ref name="PenpaarPulavargal">{{cite book | last = Govindan | first = K. | author-link = | title = பெண்பாற் புலவர்கள் [Poetess] | publisher = The South India Saiva Siddhanta Works Publishing Society | series = Sangathamil Pulavar Series - 5 | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 1953 | location = Chennai | pages = 76–81 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Contribution to the Sangam literature== Ponmudiyar has written 4 Sangam verses, including 3 in [[Purananuru]] (verses 299, 310, and 312) and 1 in [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]] (verse 14).<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3"/>
